Package com.zaxxer.nuprocess

Provides the primary classes and interfaces for executing and interacting with processes in an asynchronous manner.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
NuProcess The NuProcessBuilder.start() method creates a native process and returns an instance of a platform-specific implementation of NuProcess that can be used to control the process and obtain information about it.
NuProcessFactory This is an internal class. Instances of this interface create and start processes in a platform-specific fashion.
NuProcessHandler Executors of a NuProcess must provide an implementation of this class to the ProcessBuilder prior to calling ProcessBuilder.start().
 

Class Summary
NuAbstractProcessHandler Convenience base class for a NuProcessHandler with default methods that can be overridden.
NuProcessBuilder This class is used to create operating system processes.
 

Package com.zaxxer.nuprocess Description

Provides the primary classes and interfaces for executing and interacting with processes in an asynchronous manner.
